<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I tried to mount my USB stick formatted in NTFS. Dolphin failed to do so, with the following error message:</p> <blockquote> <p>Filesystem type ntfs3, ntfs not configured in kernel.</p> </blockquote> <p>So I tried manually with <code>sudo mount -t ntfs3 /dev/sdg1 &quot;/run/media/&lt;directory&gt;&quot;</code> (as specified in the wiki), which also failed with &quot;unknown file system ntfs3&quot;.</p> <p>I thought zen above 5.15 should have NTFS support. Do I have to enable the driver somewhere?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/l0drex"> /u/l0drex </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wczk5b/unknown_file_system_ntfs3_on_zen_kernel_51814/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wczk5b/unknown_file_system_ntfs3_on_zen_kernel_51814/">[comments]</a></span>